    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-01-14T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-01-14T05:00:00-05:00" n="899"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/56: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-01-14T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 14, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received January 14—8:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Government wishes to purchase Sperry antiaircraft searchlights to value of
                    $700,000 provided Export and Import Bank will grant credit. It is believed that
                    as credit operation no obstacles exist, Turkish Government seeks American lights
                    and will certainly purchase elsewhere if unable to close with Sperry. Please
                    cable whether nature of business will prevent Export and Import Bank from
                    assisting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
